This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a new architecture for relational networks that enables more complex relational reasoning. It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the proposed architecture involves multiple layers and joint training. Additionally, it may belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the bAbI 20 QA dataset involves natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as relational reasoning is important in tasks such as object recognition and scene understanding. Finally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the proposed architecture involves neural networks.
